ive}}</ref>\n*Arkansas: Arkansas reported the first time in almost a week that they have no new case.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ky3.com/content/news/No-new-reported-cases-of-coronavirus-in-Arkansas-568869771.html|title=No new reported cases of coronavirus in Arkansas|last=Sinett|first=Caitlin|website=ky3.com|language=english|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321135252/https://www.ky3.com/content/news/No-new-reported-cases-of-coronavirus-in-Arkansas-568869771.html|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*California: Beginning at 12:01 am on Tuesday, March 17, the counties of San Francisco, Marin, Santa Clara, Santa Cruz, San Mateo, Contra Costa, and Alameda, with a combined population of approximately 7 million people, were placed under a mandatory \"shelter in place\" order requiring everyone to stay home and all businesses to close except for those providing \"essential services\" (such as groceries, hospitals, pharmacies, banks, or delivery services), \"essential infrastructure\" (such as utilities or public transportation), or \"essential government functions\".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Har |first=Janie |url=https://apnews.com/a342998638cdccb56172a1663e8d6edf |title=San Francisco Bay Area counties issue shelter-in-place order |date=2020-03-16 |work=AP News |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318024109/https://apnews.com/a342998638cdccb56172a1663e8d6edf |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Arango |first=Tim |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/16/us/california-covid-19.html |title=To Battle Virus, 6 California Counties Order Everyone to Stay Home |date=2020-03-16 |work=The New York Times |access-date=2020-03-17 |last2=Fuller |first2=Thomas |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331 |last3=Eligon |first3=John |last4=Dougherty |first4=Conor |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318041903/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/16/us/california-covid-19.html |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*Florida: Governor of Florida announced that Florida had 24 new cases, increasing the total to 216 cases.<ref name=\"Cutway\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.clickorlando.com/news/local/2020/03/17/florida-coronavirus-cases-swells-to-216-governor-says/|title=Number of Florida coronavirus cases swells to 216, governor says|last=Cutway|first=Adrienne|date=2020-03-17|website=WKMG|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318140035/https://www.clickorlando.com/news/local/2020/03/17/florida-coronavirus-cases-swells-to-216-governor-says/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The governor also ordered business that sells liquor to reduce their occupancy by a half, and to limit parties on beaches to only 10 people per group.<ref name=\"Cutway\"/>\n* Kansas: [[Laura Kelly|Governor Laura Kelly]] ordered all K-12 schools to close for the remainder of the school year.<ref name=\"Mar17_Kansas\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.kake.com/story/41906786/kansas-orders-all-k-12-schools-to-close-for-the-rest-of-the-school-year |title=Kansas orders all K-12 schools to close for the rest of the school year |publisher=KAKE News |agency=KAKE News |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317223904/http://www.kake.com/story/41906786/kansas-orders-all-k-12-schools-to-close-for-the-rest-of-the-school-year |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*Illinois: The state announces its first death as 55 new cases are added, including 22 at a nursing home in [[Willowbrook, DuPage County, Illinois]]. The state total is now 166.<ref>[https://www.chicagotribune.com/coronavirus/ct-coronavirus-pandemic-chicago-illinois-news-20200317-hztvkm3zszfmzj7sgdege2s7z4-story.html?fbclid=IwAR1FQn2A-5JTREXdYX9mmkh__qKlflfrDRGJs1QYKp-1nbuik6viNb1SzDI Coronavirus in Illinois updates: State's 1st death from COVID-19 reported in Chicago] Chicago Tribune, 17 Mar 2020</ref>