ates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|title=Coronavirus cases surge as Northam bans gatherings of more than 10, Hogan postpones primary|last=Chason|first=Rachel|date=18 March 2020|website=Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318121502/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/maryland-virginia-dc-coronavirus-tuesday-updates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n*Michigan: The first death from coronavirus in the state is reported, a man in his 50s who had underlying medical conditions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/man-at-wayne-county-hospital-is-michigans-first-confirmed-coronavirus-death/|title=Man at Wayne County hospital is Michigan's first confirmed coronavirus death|website=clickondetroit.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318231056/https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/man-at-wayne-county-hospital-is-michigans-first-confirmed-coronavirus-death/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The state also announces 30 more confirmed cases, bringing the total number there to 110.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/michigan-officials-state-has-at-least-30-more-confirmed-cases-of-coronavirus-covid-19-bringing-total-to-110/|title=Michigan officials: State has at least 30 more confirmed cases of coronavirus (COVID-19), bringing total to 110|website=clickondetroit.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318231055/https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/michigan-officials-state-has-at-least-30-more-confirmed-cases-of-coronavirus-covid-19-bringing-total-to-110/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Minnesota: Governor Tim Walz criticized the federal response to the virus. The state had approximately 1700 frozen samples to be tes