om/homenews/state-watch/488575-california-gov-newsom-orders-all-californians-to-stay-in-homes California Gov. Newsom issues order for entire state to stay at home due to coronavirus] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320034348/https://thehill.com/homenews/state-watch/488575-california-gov-newsom-orders-all-californians-to-stay-in-homes |date=March 20, 2020 }} BY MARTY JOHNSON AND J. EDWARD MORENO, The Hill, 19 Mar 2020</ref> The [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] is considering changing its criteria for qualifications in the 2021 Oscar ceremony because so many movie theaters are closed.<ref>[https://deadline.com/2020/03/oscars-rule-changes-coronavirus-crisis-1202887971/ Oscars: Movie Academy Evaluating \"What Changes May Need To Be Made\" Amid Coronavirus Crisis] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320131422/https://deadline.com/2020/03/oscars-rule-changes-coronavirus-crisis-1202887971/ |date=March 20, 2020 }} By Anthony D'Alessandro, Matthew Carey, Deadline, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Hawaii: Two cruise ships are prevented from disembarking despite not having any cases of Covid-19 on board.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/two-cruise-ships-turned-away-145857760.html Despite no reported coronavirus, Hawaii won't let cruise ship passengers disembark] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320214212/https://news.yahoo.com/two-cruise-ships-turned-away-145857760.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by CHRISTINA CARREGA, ABC News, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Massachusetts: The [[Massachusetts Medical Society]] says there is a \"dire\" shortage of protective medical equipment in the state.<ref>[https://www.rawstory.com/2020/03/dire-shortage-of-personal-protective-equipment-reported-in-massachusetts-reports/?fbclid=IwAR2hhQhjCTatrh7HLPS8eBg9lX9RKLcZ9Yodtkqiwjrf83vCy6d9SD9ALMA \u2018Dire\u2019 shortage of personal protective equipment reported in Massachusetts: reports] By Matthew Chapman, Raw Story, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Michigan: The state reports