ille]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/coronavirus-nashville-15-patients-have-recovered-virus/2885351001/|title='Encouraging': 15 people in Nashville recovered from coronavirus, health officials say|first=Brett|last=Kelman|website=The Tennessean|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref> However, the health department confirmed the state's first death of coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/first-coronavirus-death-tennessee-reported-nashville-davidson-county/2886440001/|title=Nashville health department reports Tennessee's first coronavirus death|first=Emily R.|last=West|website=The Tennessean|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n*Texas: Dallas mega-church preacher [[Robert Jeffress]] agrees to move his Sunday services online.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-fears-force-dallas-megachurch-pastor-jeffress-to-move-services-online-211141698.html Dallas megachurch pastor Jeffress capitulates to coronavirus warnings, moves services online] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320215751/https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-fears-force-dallas-megachurch-pastor-jeffress-to-move-services-online-211141698.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Alexander Nazaryan, Yahoo News, 20 March 2020</ref>\n*Virginia: Governor Northam activated Virginia National Guard. The state announced they have 114 cases of COVID-19, with 20 hospitalizations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wydaily.com/local-news/2020/03/20/national-guard-activated-james-city-county-coronavirus-positive-cases-jumps-to-19-williamsburg-has-four-the-state-114/|title=National Guard activated: James City County coronavirus positive cases jumps to 19; Williamsburg has four; the state, 114|last=Marsigliano|first=Julia|date=2020-03-20|website=Williamsburg Yorktown Daily|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321020357/https://wydaily.com/local-news/2020/03/20/national-guard-activated-james-cit